{
  "description": "Shared Docker container-state contract fixture between fivenines-agent and fivenines-server (server issue #492). Source of truth: fivenines-agent tests/fixtures/docker_contract_payload.json, asserted end-to-end by tests/test_docker.py::test_contract_fixture_scenarios (only the Docker SDK -- containers.list / container.reload / container.stats / images.get -- is mocked). For each scenario, 'sdk' is the agent-side mock input (per-container inspect attrs + stats samples + the image objects images.get returns) and documents how the payload arises; the server ignores it. 'payload' is the exact value the agent emits under data['docker'] -- the artifact the server's DockerContainer ingester must parse. The server's spec posts each 'payload' under data['docker'] and asserts ingestion; copy this file byte-identical into the server's spec/fixtures/. Change only in lockstep. Contract highlights: (a) the identity+state block is UNCONDITIONAL -- present for every container, any status, from its first sighting; (b) stats keys (cpu/memory/block/networks) appear ONLY for a running container that has a prior stats sample (CPU-delta warm-up), so a running container's first tick is state-only too; (c) the raw blkio_stats dict is DROPPED and replaced by the clean cumulative counters block_read_bytes/block_write_bytes (the server never read blkio_stats, so removal is safe in both deploy orders); (d) collection failure emits data['docker']=null (never {}), and {'containers': {}} means GENUINELY zero containers (prune-safe).",
  "agent_min_version": "1.11.2",
  "_agent_min_version_note": "1.11.0 was taken by the Redis/Valkey deepening (server #491), 1.11.1 by log monitoring V1; container-state monitoring ships in 1.11.2. The server's FEATURES_SUPPORTED_VERSIONS[\"docker_states\"] must match this exactly.",
  "error_path_audit": {
    "connect_failure": "get_docker_client returns None (daemon down / socket refused) -> docker_metrics returns None -> data['docker'] is null. The server must never prune on null.",
    "list_failure": "client.containers.list(all=True, sparse=True) raising -> docker_metrics returns None -> data['docker'] is null. Same never-prune contract as connect failure.",
    "per_container_inspect_or_stats_failure": "container.reload() (the inspect) or container.stats() raising, or a NotFound race (container removed between list and inspect), skips ONLY that container; its siblings are still emitted. A skipped container is simply absent from this tick's payload (the server's freshness window handles a transient absence).",
    "image_metadata_failure": "client.images.get(image_id) raising (image deleted mid-tick) yields image_tags=[] and image_repo_digests=[] for that entry; the container entry itself survives with its full state block (image still carries Config.Image, image_id still carries attrs.Image).",
    "previous_stats_pruning": "the module-level previous_stats warm-up cache is pruned every tick to the set of containers seen this tick, so removed containers do not leak; a restarted container keeps the same id (warm-up preserved) while a recreated container gets a new id (warm-up restarts)."
  },
